cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DB (Databases): The paper focuses on using distributed language embedding methods to assign vectors to database entities and using these vectors to enable cognitive intelligence queries in relational databases. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper applies natural language processing techniques to database entities to generate low dimensional word embeddings. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of cognitive intelligence queries, which involve extracting information from the database based on relationships encoded by vectors. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a learning method to generate token sequences from the database and applies distributed language embedding methods to these sequences to generate vectors. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the use of vectors to enable a dual view of the data (relational and meaningful text) and to quantify semantic relationships between tokens.
